        {
          "ruleId": "tachi/ai/llm-threats",
          "message": {
            "text": "Improper output handling — SSRF via LLM-synthesized URL: the Orchestrator can instruct the MCP Tool Server to fetch external URLs synthesized from LLM output. An attacker who influences the Orchestrator's output can cause it to emit internal service URLs (cloud metadata endpoints, internal admin APIs) as tool parameters. The Tool Server fetches these with its server-side network credentials.",
            "markdown": "Implement URL allowlisting on all outbound HTTP tool invocations in the MCP Tool Server. Block egress to RFC 1918 ranges, link-local, and cloud metadata endpoints via egress firewall. Validate URL scheme to {http, https} only."
