        {
          "ruleId": "tachi/stride/tampering",
          "message": {
            "text": "The Audit Logger entries can be tampered with by a process with write access to the log store. Modifying or deleting log entries corrupts the training signal stream consumed by the Long-Running Learning Loop, causing poisoned model updates, and also destroys forensic evidence needed for incident response.",
            "markdown": "Implement the Audit Logger as an append-only store. Cryptographically hash log batches (Merkle tree) to detect any post-write modification. Store a log hash chain externally in a separate immutable store."
          },
          "level": "warning",
          "locations": [
