        {
          "ruleId": "tachi/stride/tampering",
          "message": {
            "text": "The training signal stream from the Audit Logger to the Learning Loop can be poisoned (data poisoning attack) by injecting adversarial entries into the Audit Logger before training runs. A time-delayed attack inserts adversarial training signals that activate only when a specific trigger pattern appears in future user prompts — a sleeper-agent injection via the model update cycle.",
            "markdown": "Apply training data provenance attestation: each log entry must carry a verifiable origin signature. Implement anomaly detection on training signal distributions. Limit the influence of any single data source on model parameters; implement gradient clipping and differential privacy during training."
          },
          "level": "warning",
          "locations": [
            {
              "physicalLocation": {
                "artifactLocation": { "uri": "examples/agentic-app/test-output/2026-04-23T19-30-00-F2-wave4/threats.md" },
